  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\nRunning `make all` inside `op-bindings` can be extremely slow when on a low-powered machine. I believe this is mainly because the contracts are being repeatedly recompiled (which can take upwards of a minute on a laptop PER compilation run meaning the whole process can take 10-15 minutes). Binding generation would be much faster if we only compiled the contracts once and then generated as many bindings as possible based on that one compilation.\r\n",
